    "body": "Yes, we can put the MatJax rendering code inside a function that first\nchecks to make sure that MathJax is loaded.  Don't know if that would\nhelp this issue though, but it may.\n\nOn Wed, Nov 30, 2011 at 10:50 AM, Fernando Perez\nreply@reply.github.com\nwrote:\n\n> @minrk, @ellisonbg: do you guys think we could make mathjax loading optional? There are a number of scenarios where we've seen it can cause problems, so it might be worth making it optional (if nothing else, if a user has forgotten to install it locally and they don't have internet, they're hosed and can't even open their files).  I'm making this a blocker so that at least we make a decision for 0.12, even if the decision is to for now leave it as-is... Just so it's high on our radar of things not to forget.\n> \n> I'd vote for making it optional, on by default but easy to disable...\n> \n> ---\n> \n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub:\n> https://github.com/ipython/ipython/issues/1071#issuecomment-2964247\n\n## \n\nBrian E. Granger\nCal Poly State University, San Luis Obispo\nbgranger@calpoly.edu and ellisonbg@gmail.com\n"
