    "body": "On Wed, Nov 30, 2011 at 11:07 AM, Brian E. Granger\nreply@reply.github.com\nwrote:\n\n> Yes, we can put the MatJax rendering code inside a function that first\n> checks to make sure that MathJax is loaded.  Don't know if that would\n> help this issue though, but it may.\n\nThat would already be a big improvement, since it would prevent the\nlockup problem when there's no mathjax to be found.  But I was\nactually thinking of an option to disable it altogether, for users\nwhere it may cause problems due to bringing the js engine in the\nbrowser to its knees (that's what I suspect is happening to Pauli).\n"
