    "body": "On Wed, Nov 30, 2011 at 3:29 PM, Min RK\nreply@reply.github.com\nwrote:\n\n> Quick question:  Do we want the option to be:\n> \n> a) just skip MathJax if no _local_ MathJax is available\n> b) skip MathJax altogether\n> \n> a) protects local users with a slow network connection\n> b) also protects users who may have a slow connection to the _server_\n\nI'd say skip mathjax altogether, so that users can turn mathjax off if\nthey are going to work on some giant notebook on a slow machine, but\notherwise normally keep it on.  As long as this is a configurable,\nit's easy for them to either make a profile with it or an alias.\n"
